			<STRING> ([Chinese: 秦始皇, Pinyin: Qín Shǐ Huáng, Wade-Giles: Ch'in Shih-huang]) (November / December 260 BCE – September 10, 210 BCE), personal name Zheng, was king of the Chinese State of Qin from 247 BCE to 221 BCE, and then the first emperor of a unified China from 221 BCE to 210 BCE, ruling under the name First Emperor. </STRING>
